{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780741808017,"sessionID":"ses_16384c52effeHJzY2mg4EmA5Ud","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_31af11793cab4e5a91334c3e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/lineages"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/lineages</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\ndeepseek-risk/\nmimo-risk/\n\n(2 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":"deepseek-risk/\nmimo-risk/","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/lineages","entries":["deepseek-risk/","mimo-risk/"],"offset":1,"totalEntries":2,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/lineages","time":{"start":1780741808014,"end":1780741808016}},"id":"prt_e9c7b9f8b001fzCFgQZFW8MBe9","sessionID":"ses_16384c52effeHJzY2mg4EmA5Ud","messageID":"msg_e9c7b7e6d0017CFUXLh5e2Jvte"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780741808589,"sessionID":"ses_16384c52effeHJzY2mg4EmA5Ud","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_5b14d992386e4fcfa92122bd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy — Run 3: Risk Resolution (pre-implementation)\n2: \n3: ## Topic\n4: \n5: Resolve EVERY risk and unknown in the spec-memory dual-stack CLI design before implementation. Convergence-driven: lanes stop when all questions reach a terminal classification, hard cap 20 iterations per lane.\n6: \n7: ## Premise (settled by runs 1–2 — read as input, do not relitigate)\n8: \n9: - Run 1: GO — CLI over the existing daemon/IPC with auto-spawn; zero feature loss; daemon must stay (`../research.md`).\n10: - Run 2: the CLI design — `.opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs` shim + compiled `mcp_server/spec-memory-cli.ts`, subcommands generated from `TOOL_DEFINITIONS`, exits 0/1/64/69/75 (`../cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md`).\n11: \n12: ## Exclusion\n13: \n14: Do NOT read sibling lane folders under `risk-resolution/lineages/` (only your own). Findings derived from a sibling lane are void.\n15: \n16: ## Done-Definition\n17: \n18: Every key question (seed + newly added) must end as one of:\n19: - **RESOLVED** — answered with file:line or measured evidence\n20: - **MITIGATED** — a named design delta the implementation packet must absorb\n21: - **ACCEPTED** — risk consciously accepted with explicit rationale\n22: - **DEFERRED** — blocked on a named external dependency\n23: \n24: Unclassified = not done. Add newly discovered risks as new key questions; they need terminal classification too.\n25: \n26: ## Key Questions\n27: \n28: - [ ] RQ1: Daemon-bypass enforcement — public CLI provably IPC-only? Admin direct-DB path inventory; unix-socket trust model + socket permissions.\n29: - [ ] RQ2: Schema-drift mechanics — all 37 arg shapes round-trip via argv + `--json`? Codegen feasibility from TOOL_DEFINITIONS; tools that don't map cleanly.\n30: - [ ] RQ3: Lease/spawn races — CLI auto-spawn vs MCP-owned daemon; simultaneous CLI spawns; CLI-spawned daemon lifetime/reaping/orphan risk (six orphaned mk-skill-advisor launchers observed today).\n31: - [ ] RQ4: Retryable taxonomy — complete error→exit map (-32001, cold-start, lease contention, SQLITE_BUSY; 75 vs 69).\n32: - [ ] RQ5: Hook latency budget — daemon-down cold path (auto-spawn + 15–30s embedder warm) vs per-runtime hook timeout ceilings; which hook types can shell out.\n33: - [ ] RQ6: Per-call spawn overhead — MEASURE node startup + socket round-trip on this host; validate the 50–150ms estimate.\n34: - [ ] RQ7: Session-identity semantics — sessionId propagation verified in dedup/learning/working-memory code paths; what non-codex runtimes pass.\n35: - [ ] RQ8: Build/activation drift — shim→dist staleness; launcher bootstrap-lock coverage of the CLI handoff.\n36: - [ ] RQ9: Dual-client load — MCP+CLI simultaneous traffic contention; existing stress-test coverage vs gaps.\n37: - [ ] RQ10: Effort reconciliation — one defensible dual-stack estimate (8–12d vs 13–16d vs 3–4wk).\n38: - [ ] RQ11: Platform/socket constraints — macOS sun_path limit handling; Windows non-goal decision.\n39: \n40: ## Known Context\n41: \n42: - The daemon IPC bridge serves multiple concurrent clients (test-proven); owner lease is the single-writer boundary.\n43: - `generate-context.js` performed a full indexed save with the MCP down on 2026-06-06 (CLI-path precedent).\n44: - The 2026-06-06 disconnect incident: owner-exit left the daemon down; Claude Code never reconnects MCP mid-session.\n45: - Read-only bash timing measurements are permitted; file mutation is not.\n46: \n47: ## Negative Knowledge (ruled out)\n48: \n49: - Pure per-invocation CLI (run 1); MCP removal (non-goal — dual-stack).\n50: \n51: ## Next Focus\n52: \n53: Iteration 1: RQ1 + RQ3 (the two HIGH-severity structural risks). Then proceed by severity, adding discovered risks as new RQs.\n54: \n55: ## Parameters\n56: \n57: - Max iterations: 20 per lane (terminal cap)\n58: - Convergence threshold: 0.05 (genuine convergence active; all-questions-classified is the intended exit)\n\n(End of file - total 58 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy — Run 3: Risk Resolution (pre-implementation)\n\n## Topic\n\nResolve EVERY risk and unknown in the spec-memory dual-stack CLI design before implementation. Convergence-driven: lanes stop when all questions reach a terminal classification, hard cap 20 iterations per lane.\n\n## Premise (settled by runs 1–2 — read as input, do not relitigate)\n\n- Run 1: GO — CLI over the existing daemon/IPC with auto-spawn; zero feature loss; daemon must stay (`../research.md`).\n- Run 2: the CLI design — `.opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs` shim + compiled `mcp_server/spec-memory-cli.ts`, subcommands generated from `TOOL_DEFINITIONS`, exits 0/1/64/69/75 (`../cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md`).\n\n## Exclusion\n\nDo NOT read sibling lane folders under `risk-resolution/lineages/` (only your own). Findings derived from a sibling lane are void.\n\n## Done-Definition\n\nEvery key question (seed + newly added) must end as one of:\n- **RESOLVED** — answered with file:line or measured evidence\n- **MITIGATED** — a named design delta the implementation packet must absorb","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy — Run 3: Risk Resolution (pre-implementation)\n\n## Topic\n\nResolve EVERY risk and unknown in the spec-memory dual-stack CLI design before implementation. Convergence-driven: lanes stop when all questions reach a terminal classification, hard cap 20 iterations per lane.\n\n## Premise (settled by runs 1–2 — read as input, do not relitigate)\n\n- Run 1: GO — CLI over the existing daemon/IPC with auto-spawn; zero feature loss; daemon must stay (`../research.md`).\n- Run 2: the CLI design — `.opencode/bin/spec-memory.cjs` shim + compiled `mcp_server/spec-memory-cli.ts`, subcommands generated from `TOOL_DEFINITIONS`, exits 0/1/64/69/75 (`../cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md`).\n\n## Exclusion\n\nDo NOT read sibling lane folders under `risk-resolution/lineages/` (only your own). Findings derived from a sibling lane are void.\n\n## Done-Definition\n\nEvery key question (seed + newly added) must end as one of:\n- **RESOLVED** — answered with file:line or measured evidence\n- **MITIGATED** — a named design delta the implementation packet must absorb\n- **ACCEPTED** — risk consciously accepted with explicit rationale\n- **DEFERRED** — blocked on a named external dependency\n\nUnclassified = not done. Add newly discovered risks as new key questions; they need terminal classification too.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- [ ] RQ1: Daemon-bypass enforcement — public CLI provably IPC-only? Admin direct-DB path inventory; unix-socket trust model + socket permissions.\n- [ ] RQ2: Schema-drift mechanics — all 37 arg shapes round-trip via argv + `--json`? Codegen feasibility from TOOL_DEFINITIONS; tools that don't map cleanly.\n- [ ] RQ3: Lease/spawn races — CLI auto-spawn vs MCP-owned daemon; simultaneous CLI spawns; CLI-spawned daemon lifetime/reaping/orphan risk (six orphaned mk-skill-advisor launchers observed today).\n- [ ] RQ4: Retryable taxonomy — complete error→exit map (-32001, cold-start, lease contention, SQLITE_BUSY; 75 vs 69).\n- [ ] RQ5: Hook latency budget — daemon-down cold path (auto-spawn + 15–30s embedder warm) vs per-runtime hook timeout ceilings; which hook types can shell out.\n- [ ] RQ6: Per-call spawn overhead — MEASURE node startup + socket round-trip on this host; validate the 50–150ms estimate.\n- [ ] RQ7: Session-identity semantics — sessionId propagation verified in dedup/learning/working-memory code paths; what non-codex runtimes pass.\n- [ ] RQ8: Build/activation drift — shim→dist staleness; launcher bootstrap-lock coverage of the CLI handoff.\n- [ ] RQ9: Dual-client load — MCP+CLI simultaneous traffic contention; existing stress-test coverage vs gaps.\n- [ ] RQ10: Effort reconciliation — one defensible dual-stack estimate (8–12d vs 13–16d vs 3–4wk).\n- [ ] RQ11: Platform/socket constraints — macOS sun_path limit handling; Windows non-goal decision.\n\n## Known Context\n\n- The daemon IPC bridge serves multiple concurrent clients (test-proven); owner lease is the single-writer boundary.\n- `generate-context.js` performed a full indexed save with the MCP down on 2026-06-06 (CLI-path precedent).\n- The 2026-06-06 disconnect incident: owner-exit left the daemon down; Claude Code never reconnects MCP mid-session.\n- Read-only bash timing measurements are permitted; file mutation is not.\n\n## Negative Knowledge (ruled out)\n\n- Pure per-invocation CLI (run 1); MCP removal (non-goal — dual-stack).\n\n## Next Focus\n\nIteration 1: RQ1 + RQ3 (the two HIGH-severity structural risks). Then proceed by severity, adding discovered risks as new RQs.\n\n## Parameters\n\n- Max iterations: 20 per lane (terminal cap)\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05 (genuine convergence active; all-questions-classified is the intended exit)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":58,"totalLines":58,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1780741808584,"end":1780741808588}},"id":"prt_e9c7ba1c6001SBppwUYlx1qE9y","sessionID":"ses_16384c52effeHJzY2mg4EmA5Ud","messageID":"msg_e9c7b7e6d0017CFUXLh5e2Jvte"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780741809207,"sessionID":"ses_16384c52effeHJzY2mg4EmA5Ud","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_05eebd6abb12462789dcc1fa","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-config.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-config.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"topic\": \"Run 3 — RISK RESOLUTION before implementation of the spec-memory dual-stack CLI. PREMISE (settled, do not relitigate): run-1 GO verdict in ../research.md and the run-2 CLI design in ../cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md — READ BOTH as input. EXCLUSION: do not read anything under this run's sibling lineages directory (research/risk-resolution/lineages/ other than your own lane folder); findings derived from a sibling lane are void. MISSION: investigate EVERY risk and unknown below until each is classified RESOLVED (with file:line or measured evidence), MITIGATED (named design delta the implementation packet must absorb), ACCEPTED (explicit rationale), or DEFERRED (named blocker) — and ADD any newly discovered risks/unknowns as new key questions which must also reach a terminal classification. The loop is done only when every question is classified; read-only timing measurements via bash are allowed, file mutation is not. The seed register: RQ1 daemon-bypass enforcement — can the public CLI provably never open the database directly; inventory every admin direct-DB path; the unix-socket trust model (which local processes can connect; socket file permissions). RQ2 schema-drift mechanics — do all 37 tool arg shapes (nested objects, arrays, unions) round-trip via argv flags plus a --json escape hatch; is codegen from TOOL_DEFINITIONS feasible for every tool; enumerate the tools whose schemas do not map cleanly to flags. RQ3 lease/spawn races — CLI auto-spawn while an MCP session owns the daemon; two CLIs spawning simultaneously; lifetime and ownership of a CLI-spawned daemon when no MCP session exists (who reaps it, idle timeout, orphan risk — six orphaned mk-skill-advisor launchers were observed on this host today as a cautionary precedent). RQ4 retryable taxonomy — the complete error-to-exit-75 map: -32001, cold-start exhaustion, lease contention, SQLITE_BUSY; which daemon errors are genuinely retryable versus terminal (exit 69). RQ5 hook latency budget — ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n3:   \"maxIterations\": 20,\n4:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n5:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n6:   \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n7:   \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n8:   \"resource_map_present\": false,\n9:   \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": false },\n10:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T10:28:38Z\",\n11:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n12:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n13:   \"lineage\": {\n14:     \"sessionId\": \"dr-20260606T122838-risk-resolution\",\n15:     \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-20260606T120541-cli-backend\",\n16:     \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n17:     \"generation\": 1,\n18:     \"continuedFromRun\": null\n19:   },\n20:   \"fanout\": {\n21:     \"executors\": [\n22:       { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"deepseek-risk\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 20 },\n23:       { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"mimo-risk\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 20 }\n24:     ],\n25:     \"concurrency\": 2\n26:   }\n27: }\n\n(End of file - total 27 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"topic\": \"Run 3 — RISK RESOLUTION before implementation of the spec-memory dual-stack CLI. PREMISE (settled, do not relitigate): run-1 GO verdict in ../research.md and the run-2 CLI design in ../cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md — READ BOTH as input. EXCLUSION: do not read anything under this run's sibling lineages directory (research/risk-resolution/lineages/ other than your own lane folder); findings derived from a sibling lane are void. MISSION: investigate EVERY risk and unknown below until each is classified RESOLVED (with file:line or measured evidence), MITIGATED (named design delta the implementation packet must absorb), ACCEPTED (explicit rationale), or DEFERRED (named blocker) — and ADD any newly discovered risks/unknowns as new key questions which must also reach a terminal classification. The loop is done only when every question is classified; read-only timing measurements via bash are allowed, file mutation is not. The seed register: RQ1 daemon-bypass enforcement — can the public CLI provably never open the database directly; inventory every admin direct-DB path; the unix-socket trust model (which local processes can connect; socket file permissions). RQ2 schema-drift mechanics — do all 37 tool arg shapes (nested objects, arrays, unions) round-trip via argv flags plus a --json escape hatch; is codegen from TOOL_DEFINITIONS feasible for every tool; enumerate the tools whose schemas do not map cleanly to flags. RQ3 lease/spawn races — CLI auto-spawn while an MCP session owns the daemon; two CLIs spawning simultaneously; lifetime and ownership of a CLI-spawned daemon when no MCP session exists (who reaps it, idle timeout, orphan risk — six orphaned mk-skill-advisor launchers were observed on this host today as a cautionary precedent). RQ4 retryable taxonomy — the complete error-to-exit-75 map: -32001, cold-start exhaustion, lease contention, SQLITE_BUSY; which daemon errors are genuinely retryable versus terminal (exit 69). RQ5 hook latency budget — ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n  \"maxIterations\": 20,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n  \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": false },\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T10:28:38Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"dr-20260606T122838-risk-resolution\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-20260606T120541-cli-backend\",\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"fanout\": {","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/risk-resolution/deep-research-config.json","text":"{\n  \"topic\": \"Run 3 — RISK RESOLUTION before implementation of the spec-memory dual-stack CLI. PREMISE (settled, do not relitigate): run-1 GO verdict in ../research.md and the run-2 CLI design in ../cli-backend/lineages/gpt/research.md — READ BOTH as input. EXCLUSION: do not read anything under this run's sibling lineages directory (research/risk-resolution/lineages/ other than your own lane folder); findings derived from a sibling lane are void. MISSION: investigate EVERY risk and unknown below until each is classified RESOLVED (with file:line or measured evidence), MITIGATED (named design delta the implementation packet must absorb), ACCEPTED (explicit rationale), or DEFERRED (named blocker) — and ADD any newly discovered risks/unknowns as new key questions which must also reach a terminal classification. The loop is done only when every question is classified; read-only timing measurements via bash are allowed, file mutation is not. The seed register: RQ1 daemon-bypass enforcement — can the public CLI provably never open the database directly; inventory every admin direct-DB path; the unix-socket trust model (which local processes can connect; socket file permissions). RQ2 schema-drift mechanics — do all 37 tool arg shapes (nested objects, arrays, unions) round-trip via argv flags plus a --json escape hatch; is codegen from TOOL_DEFINITIONS feasible for every tool; enumerate the tools whose schemas do not map cleanly to flags. RQ3 lease/spawn races — CLI auto-spawn while an MCP session owns the daemon; two CLIs spawning simultaneously; lifetime and ownership of a CLI-spawned daemon when no MCP session exists (who reaps it, idle timeout, orphan risk — six orphaned mk-skill-advisor launchers were observed on this host today as a cautionary precedent). RQ4 retryable taxonomy — the complete error-to-exit-75 map: -32001, cold-start exhaustion, lease contention, SQLITE_BUSY; which daemon errors are genuinely retryable versus terminal (exit 69). RQ5 hook latency budget — ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n  \"maxIterations\": 20,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n  \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": false },\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T10:28:38Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"dr-20260606T122838-risk-resolution\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-20260606T120541-cli-backend\",\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"fanout\": {\n    \"executors\": [\n      { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"deepseek-risk\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 20 },\n      { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"mimo-risk\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 20 }\n    ],\n    \"concurrency\": 2\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":27,"totalLines":27,"truncated":fal